    "The more data is employed to identify hidden patterns, the more energy-intensive the process becomes.",
    "Second, lithium is a mineral crucial for building the rechargeable batteries that power wireless devices.",
    "Such devices, which range from mobile phones to smart assistants, are key facilitators of AI as they make it possible to generate the data required to train AI algorithms and to enable AI-powered applications.",
    "Electric vehicles, which currently drive most of the demand for lithium (Jerez et al. 2021), have been deemed as 'green technologies'; paradoxically, the extraction of lithium in the Atacama Desert, one of the driest areas of the world, employs vast amounts of water.",
